Let $r$ be the annual interest rate as a decimal.  Then the total amount of money in the account after three years is $20,000(1+r)^3$.  We want this to be at least $66,200$, so we can solve for $r$:

\begin{align*}
20,000(1+r)^3&\ge 66200\\
\Rightarrow\qquad (1+r)^3&\ge 33.1\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 1+r&\ge \sqrt[3]{33.1}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad r&\ge \sqrt[3]{33.1}-1\\
\Rightarrow\qquad r&\ge 0.0946\\
\Rightarrow\qquad r&=\boxed{9.46}
\end{align*}
The answer is \boxed{9.46}.

