We can use the Extended Euclidean Algorithm to find the modular inverse of $997$ modulo $1000$. First, we write the Euclidean Algorithm:

\begin{align*}
1000&=1\cdot 997+3\\
997&=332\cdot 3+1
\end{align*}

Now, we can write the Euclidean Algorithm backwards:

\begin{align*}
