&\equiv 1\cdot 997-1\cdot 3\cdot 997+1\cdot 3\cdot 332\\
&\equiv 2\cdot 997-1\cdot 3\cdot 997\\
&\equiv -1\cdot 3\cdot 997\\
&\equiv -3\cdot 997\pmod{1000}
\end{align*}

Therefore, $997^{-1} \equiv -3 \equiv \boxed{\boxed{997}} \pmod{1000}$.

The answer is \boxed{997}.

